Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}.

Toss bell pepper on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add @Italian pork sausage{9%oz} to opposite side of sheet and drizzle with olive oil. Roast on top rack until bell pepper is browned and tender and sausage is cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{8-10%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

Melt @butter{2%tbsp} (3 TBSP for 4 servings) in pot used for pasta over medium-high heat. Stir in @flour{1%tbsp} and @garlic powder{1%tsp} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Slowly whisk in @milk{6.75%oz}, ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4), and @chicken stock concentrate{1} until combined. Bring mixture to a boil, then remove from heat. Stir in @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} until melted. Season generously with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Once sausage is done, remove from oven and let cool slightly. Transfer to a #cutting board{} and slice on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Add to pot with sauce along with bell pepper and pasta. Stir, adding splashes of reserved pasta cooking water as needed, until creamy. Season generously with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Transfer mixture to an 8-by-8-inch #baking dish{} (for 4 servings, use a 9-by-13-inch dish).

Preheat broiler to high. In a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then sprinkle over pasta mixture. Broil on top rack until panko is golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch carefully for any burning.

Drizzle with as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like and serve.